- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper investigates the performance of the solvers on a multi-threaded architecture, which suggests a parallel computing aspect. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software): The paper discusses the implementation and comparison of two numerical methods for solving a specific mathematical problem. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper may touch upon software engineering aspects related to the implementation and optimization of the solvers. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): Although not directly related to machine learning, the paper may involve some aspects of optimization and iterative methods that are commonly used in machine learning.
